  <main>
    <section class="legal-hero">
      <p class="eyebrow accent-violet">Effective July 9, 2026</p>
      <h1>Apple Ledger Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="lead">A local-first finance app for ledgers, accounts, budgets, reports, recurring records, subscriptions, and private iCloud sync.</p>
      <div class="legal-actions">
        <a class="button secondary" href="../apps/appleledger.html">Apple Ledger</a>
        <a class="button secondary" href="../support/appleledger.html">Support</a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <article class="legal-layout">

      <h2>Data We Collect</h2>
      <p>The current version of Apple Ledger does not include advertising SDKs, does not include third-party analytics SDKs, does not sell user data, and does not require a developer-operated account.</p>

      <h2>Financial Data You Enter</h2>
      <p>Apple Ledger stores the ledgers, accounts, categories, tags, merchants, projects, members, transactions, budgets, recurring templates, subscriptions, credit-card details, installment records, exchange rates, notes, and related settings you create in the app.</p>

      <h2>Local Storage and iCloud</h2>
      <p>Your finance data is stored locally on your device. If you enable iCloud sync, the app syncs data through your private iCloud account using CloudKit.</p>

      <h2>Import and Export</h2>
      <p>The app can import or export JSON and CSV files when you choose those actions.</p>

      <h2>Biometric Lock</h2>
      <p>Apple Ledger can use Face ID, Touch ID, or device authentication to lock the app. Biometric authentication is handled by iOS, iPadOS, or macOS; the app does not receive your biometric data.</p>

      <h2>Notifications</h2>
      <p>The app may use local notifications for subscription reminders, recurring entries, and budget reminders when you grant notification permission.</p>
      <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
      <p>Apple Ledger is not directed to children and does not knowingly collect personal information from children.</p>
      <h2>Changes</h2>
      <p>If a future version adds accounts, developer-operated cloud sync, analytics, crash reporting, payments, advertising, or other data collection, this policy and the App Store privacy labels will be updated.</p>
      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>For privacy questions, contact <a href="mailto:support@your-domain.example">support@your-domain.example</a>.</p>
    </article>
  </main>

